# BD68 Dev v1.1 Codex Bootstrap

- Use skill `bd_dev_kit` as the default operating profile for BD68/WildSoul work.
- Prefer retrieval-first flow: `chub` (Context7 fallback, Serena for local code).
- For third-party API docs, keep `chub` as default and use Context7 only as fallback/accelerator when `chub` has no actionable result.
- For local code retrieval/edit, prefer `serena` once onboarded.
- Use gstack only as lightweight orchestration gates (`product-gate`, `engineering-gate`, `ship-gate`) and never all-ways-on.
- Do not let gstack overlap with `lint-and-validate`, `webapp-testing`, or `github`.
- If retrieval does not provide verifiable evidence for a technical claim, answer `không đủ dữ liệu` instead of guessing.
- Preferred anti-guessing libraries for Python agent flows: `pydantic-ai`, `instructor`, `langsmith` (`langgraph` optional for orchestration-heavy workflows).
- Apply 5-skill add-on gate: always-on `context-optimization` + `context-window-management`; enable `context-compression` only for large input (`>= 120k`), `prompt-caching` only for repetitive traffic (`cache hit >= 30%`), and `hierarchical-agent-memory` only for stable multi-session tasks.
- Guard Context runtime path is expected through local thread `127.0.0.1:8787` when enabled.

## Project Overlay
At session start, check if `.bd68/PROJECT.md` exists in the current working directory.
If it exists:
  - Load it AFTER BD68_PROFILE
  - Values in PROJECT.md override global profile where specified
  - `docs:` entries define preferred retrieval sources for this project
  - `locked:` entries are architecture decisions — never suggest changing them
  - `never:` entries are hard constraints — never violate them
  - `active_context:` gives current milestone and focus — use to prioritize responses
If it does not exist, proceed with global BD68_PROFILE only.

## Skill & MCP Installation Policy
When user requests adding a new skill, MCP, or any installable component:

STEP 1 — Confirm target before acting:
  Ask: "Cài global (mọi project dùng) hay chỉ project này?"
  Default nếu user không nói rõ: global → ~/.codex/skills/<skill-name>/

STEP 2 — Install theo target:
  Global skill:        ~/.codex/skills/<skill-name>/SKILL.md
  Global MCP:          ~/.codex/config or mcp config (per tool convention)
  Project-only note:   .bd68/PROJECT.md → thêm vào section key_libs hoặc docs

STEP 3 — Sau khi install global:
  Remind user:
  "Đã cài global. Nếu muốn sync vào source kit, chạy:
   install-agent-pack.ps1 -Target codex
   từ thư mục bd_dev_kit."

NEVER:
  - Cài trực tiếp vào project folder mà không hỏi
  - Giả định target mà không confirm
  - Bỏ qua bước remind sync sau install global

